HEADWORD: Endostosis
<hw>En`dos*to"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Endo-</er>, and <er>Ostosis</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>A process of bone formation in which ossification takes place
within the substance of the cartilage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endostyle</ent>⟦br⟧
